decisions[8]{id,statement,rationale}:
  PL-01, FT-06 is the dependency root and must execute first because it produces content that FT-02/FT-03/FT-05 absorb, workflow-subagent.md contains bash categories (SF-01) and retry protocol (SF-02) that move to rules.md and context handoff (SF-03) that stays in orchestrator.md. Executing FT-06 first prevents merge conflicts
  PL-02, FT-10 docs merge uses structure-first layout: Directory Structure then Naming then Per-Phase Docs then Scope/Artifacts, docs-structure provides the WHERE (directory layout) and docs-phases provides the WHEN (phase-by-phase creation guide). Unified flow eliminates the need for cross-references between the two files
  PL-03, Phase Table (34 lines) in workflow-phases.md is deleted entirely rather than compressed because CLAUDE.md Sec2 contains the authoritative 30-phase listing with identical information, keeping a compressed version would still be redundant. The Phase Work Descriptions (91 lines) are the only skill-file-unique content worth preserving
  PL-04, IA-1~7 section (38 lines) and Traceability section (32 lines) in workflow-gates.md are deleted because CLAUDE.md Sec7 and Sec10 contain identical definitions, gates.md retains Control Levels (L1-L4) and DoD table which are not in CLAUDE.md and UI-1~7 which has additional detail beyond CLAUDE.md Sec7
  PL-05, Error-type to improvement-request conversion table (10 lines) from workflow-subagent.md is preserved in workflow-execution.md because it is the only content not dynamically generated by MCPserver buildRetryPrompt, this table guides Orchestrator behavior when constructing retry instructions and has no equivalent in CLAUDE.md or MCP templates
  PL-06, Bash security category (npm audit/snyk/semgrep/trivy) is absorbed into workflow-rules.md Sec7 because SD-03 designates rules.md as the single source for all bash category definitions adding 1 line to the existing category table. The security category currently only exists in workflow-subagent.md
  PL-07, Environment Variables table (9 lines) from workflow-docs-structure.md is dropped rather than moved to operations.md because DOCS_BASE/DOCS_DIR/STATE_DIR defaults are documented in CLAUDE.md and harness source code. Only VALIDATE_DESIGN_STRICT=false is operational but rarely used and can be documented inline when needed
  PL-08, CDD+TDD Cycle diagram (13 lines) from workflow-docs-phases.md is dropped because the per-phase document tables already specify CDD integration (test_impl stories / implementation green) making the diagram redundant. The Document Creation Flow text (compressed) provides sufficient sequencing information

